<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910408-0072</DOCNO><DOCID>910408-0072.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- SpecTran Corp.:   Two-Year Supply Contracts   Set With Two Customers</HL><DATE>04/08/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7A</SO><CO>   SPTR</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>INDUSTRIAL TECHNOLOGY andamp; PRODUCTION, QUALITY CONTROL (ITC)</IN><RE>MASSACHUSETTS (MA)</RE><LP>   SpecTran Corp., Sturbridge, Mass., said it signed separatetwo-year agreements with two customers that will result insales of about $9 million in 1991 and &quot;a similar amount&quot; nextyear.   The maker of glass optical fibers said the fiber-supplycontracts increased its backlog to about $24 million as ofMarch 31. The agreements cover several of SpecTran's fiberproducts, which are expected to be used in a &quot;variety ofcustomer premise and data communications applications,&quot; thecompany added.</LP><TEXT>   In 1990, SpecTran earned $984,000, or 21 cents a share, onrevenue of $10.5 million.</TEXT></DOC>